<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFColin_R._Blyth1972">Colin R. Blyth (June 1972). "On Simpson's Paradox and the Sure-Thing Principle". <i>Journal of the American Statistical Association</i> <b>67</b> (338): 364–366. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F2284382" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F2284382" rel="nofollow">10.2307/2284382</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=On+Simpson%27s+Paradox+and+the+Sure-Thing+Principle&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+the+American+Statistical+Association&amp;rft.aulast=Colin+R.+Blyth&amp;rft.au=Colin+R.+Blyth&amp;rft.date=June+1972&amp;rft.volume=67&amp;rft.issue=338&amp;rft.pages=364%E2%80%93366&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.2307%2F2284382&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Simpson%27s_paradox"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
